{"name": "pyromark", "metadata": {"name": "pyromark", "version": "0.7.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: MacOS", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["typing-extensions"], "summary": "Blazingly fast Markdown parser", "upload_time": 1732626992}, "documentation": ["# pyromark\n\n[![CI](https://github.com/monosans/pyromark/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/monosans/pyromark/actions/workflows/ci.yml)\n[![Downloads](https://static.pepy.tech/badge/pyromark)](https://pepy.tech/project/pyromark)\n\npyromark (stands for Python Rust Optimized Markdown) is a blazingly fast CommonMark-compliant Markdown parser for Python.\n\nUses [pulldown-cmark](https://github.com/raphlinus/pulldown-cmark) Rust crate under the hood.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install -U pyromark\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n<https://pyromark.readthedocs.io>\n\n### Basic examples\n\nSee documentation for more comprehensive examples.\n\n#### Convert Markdown to HTML\n\n```python\nimport pyromark\n\nhtml = pyromark.html(\"# Hello world\")\nassert html == \"<h1>Hello world</h1>\\n\"\n```\n\n#### Iterating over Markdown elements\n\n```python\nimport pyromark\n\nfor event in pyromark.events(\"# Hello world\"):\n    # All event types are fully type annotated\n    # so you will get static type checking\n    # and Tab completions in your IDE!\n    match event:\n        case {\"Start\": {\"Heading\": {\"level\": heading_level}}}:\n            print(f\"Heading with {heading_level} level started\")\n        case {\"Text\": text}:\n            print(f\"Got {text!r} text\")\n        case {\"End\": {\"Heading\": heading_level}}:\n            print(f\"Heading with {heading_level} level ended\")\n        case other_event:\n            print(f\"Got {other_event!r}\")\n```\n\n## Performance\n\n130x faster than [Markdown](https://pypi.org/project/Markdown/),\n101x faster than [markdown-it-py](https://pypi.org/project/markdown-it-py/),\n71x faster than [mistune](https://pypi.org/project/mistune/),\n8x faster than [markdown-it-pyrs](https://pypi.org/project/markdown-it-pyrs/).\n\nIf you use threading, the difference with other libraries will be even more enormous, since pyromark releases the [GIL](https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html#term-global-interpreter-lock).\n\nSee [benchmark](https://pyromark.readthedocs.io/en/latest/performance/).\n\n## License\n\n[MIT](https://github.com/monosans/pyromark/blob/main/LICENSE)\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "python.pyromark", "documentation": ["Blazingly fast Markdown parser."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "python.pyromark.events", "xref": {"fqname": "pyromark._pyromark.events", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.pyromark.html", "xref": {"fqname": "pyromark._pyromark.html", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.pyromark.Markdown", "xref": {"fqname": "pyromark._pyromark.Markdown", "project": null}}, {"name": "python.pyromark.Options", "xref": {"fqname": "pyromark._options.Options", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options", "bases": ["IntFlag"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_TABLES", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://github.github.com/gfm/#tables-extension->"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_FOOTNOTES", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.12.2/pulldown_cmark/struct.Options.html#associatedconstant.ENABLE_FOOTNOTES>"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_STRIKETHROUGH", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://github.github.com/gfm/#strikethrough-extension->"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_TASKLISTS", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://github.github.com/gfm/#task-list-items-extension->"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_SMART_PUNCTUATION", "type": null, "documentation": ["Converts some characters to their HTML equivalents:\n\n| Character | Replacements |\n| --------- | ------------ |\n| '         | \u2018 \u2019          |\n| \"         | \u201c \u201d          |\n| ...       | \u2026            |\n| --        | \u2013            |\n| ---       | \u2014            |"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_HEADING_ATTRIBUTES", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.12.2/pulldown_cmark/struct.Options.html#associatedconstant.ENABLE_HEADING_ATTRIBUTES>"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_YAML_STYLE_METADATA_BLOCKS", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.12.2/pulldown_cmark/struct.Options.html#associatedconstant.ENABLE_YAML_STYLE_METADATA_BLOCKS>"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_PLUSES_DELIMITED_METADATA_BLOCKS", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.12.2/pulldown_cmark/struct.Options.html#associatedconstant.ENABLE_PLUSES_DELIMITED_METADATA_BLOCKS>"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_OLD_FOOTNOTES", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.12.2/pulldown_cmark/struct.Options.html#associatedconstant.ENABLE_OLD_FOOTNOTES>"]}, {"name": "python.pyromark._options.Options.ENABLE_MATH", "type": null, "documentation": ["<https